<SECOND>PM-People-Goldwater,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Goldwater Reported Doing Fine After Hip Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Sen. Barry Goldwater was doing fine after
hip surgery, a hospital spokesman said.
   Surgery was performed Wednesday on the 80-year-old Arizona
Republican's left hip, said Courd Koebergen, a spokesman for St.
Luke's Medical Center.
   He said he did not know how long Goldwater would be hospitalized.
   Goldwater, the patriarch of the GOP's conservative wing, has had
problems with an arthritic hip and knee for years.
   Goldwater underwent knee surgery at St. Luke's in April 1987, to
relive pain stemming from a college football injury. He underwent
hip operations in 1976 and 1981 and had corrective hip surgery in
April 1986.
   He also underwent triple-bypass heart surgery in 1982.
</TEXT>
