<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     07-10 0399</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0413</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Develop Over Michigan, Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms dampened northern Michigan early today and
scattered showers and thunderstorms doused much of Wyoming and
western Montana.
   Collapsing thunderstorms produced strong winds in Wyoming Sunday
evening, with gusts up to 63 mph at Rawlins.
   Widely scattered showers and thunderstorms which developed over
the southern Rockies ended late Sunday. One strong thunderstorm over
Arizona produced high winds that downed trees and power lines at
Winkelman.
   Showers and thunderstorms scattered from the eastern Gulf Coast
to the middle Atlantic Coast also dissipated late Sunday.
   In Georgia, showers and thunderstorms produced nearly 1{ inches
of rain around Atlanta Sunday night, but lingered mainly over the
southeastern part of the state this morning.
   Fair weather prevailed across most of the nation early today,
with hazy conditions over parts of the East.
   Milwaukee-area public beaches and swimming pools were packed
Sunday as the temperature soared to 95.
   ``We're ... going through a lot of chlorine,'' said Dan Shipman,
pool operator at Gordon Park. ``They don't stop coming.''
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over the
lower Great Lakes, the northern Atlantic Coast, the northern Rockies
and the lower Missouri Valley; and sunny skies elsewhere.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s in Maine, upper Michigan,
Washington, most of Oregon and part of the California coast; in the
90s across most of the southern two-thirds of the nation; in the
100s in the desert Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 47
degrees at Klamath Falls, Ore., to 91 degrees at Glendale, Ariz.,
and Las Vegas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 72 cloudy; Boston 66 fair; Buffalo 74 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 74 fair; Cincinnati 76 foggy; Cleveland 76 hazy;
Detroit 78 hazy; Miami 81 fair; New York 75 fair; Philadelphia 75
fair; Pittsburgh 69 foggy; Portland, Maine 62 fair; Washington 74
partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 69 cloudy; Chicago 84 hazy; Dallas-Fort Worth
80 fair; Denver 72 fair; Des Moines 80 fair; Indianapolis 76 hazy;
Kansas City 80 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 81 fair; Nashville 76
foggy; New Orleans 77 fair; St. Louis 82 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 73 fair; Anchorage 59 fair; Las Vegas 91 fair;
Los Angeles 64 fair; Phoenix 86 fair; Salt Lake City 76 partly
cloudy; San Diego 67 fair; San Francisco 56 fair; Seattle 59 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 66 partly cloudy; Toronto 73 fair.
</TEXT>
