<SECOND>PM-Gas Prices,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gas Prices Down 1{ Cents a Gallon Since Early June</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The national average price of gasoline has
fallen 1.67 cents a gallon since early June, the Lundberg Survey
reported.
   The average retail price determined by the latest biweekly survey
on July 7 was 116.76 cents a gallon, oil industry analyst Trilby
Lundberg said Sunday.
   The Lundberg Survey canvasses 12,000 gasoline stations nationwide.
   At self-service pumps, average prices per gallon were: regular
unleaded, 106.78 cents; premium unleaded, 122.52 cents; and regular
leaded, 106.12 cents.
   At full-service pumps, average prices per gallon were: regular
unleaded, 132.11 cents; premium unleaded, 144.03 cents; and regular
leaded 130.5 cents.
