<FIRST>r a PM-CyclingAccident     07-10 0207</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cycling Accident,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>Texas Man Killed, Another Hurt in Hit-and-Run</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 300 bicyclists resumed a
cross-country trek to raise money for cancer research despite a
hit-and-run accident that killed one member and injured another.
   ``It's thrown a somber pall over the whole group,'' said Bob
Carson of Oceanside, Calif. ``It took everybody down. We're like a
family. We've been together for four weeks.''
   Jeff Green, 36, of Dallas, died Sunday when he was struck on his
bicycle on Indiana 49 south of Valparaiso, the Porter County
Sheriff's Department said.
   Green and Gerald Wright, 39, of Silverdale, Wash., were riding
southbound when they were struck by a southbound car that left the
scene, police said.
   Green was pronounced dead at Porter Memorial Hospital in
Valparaiso, and Wright was treated for a broken leg and released,
police said.
   The two were among a group pedaling from Seattle to Atlantic City
to raise funds for the American Lung Association. The two men were
traveling by themselves on the 35th day of the journey when the
accident occurred.
   The other riders found out about Green's death at the halfway
point between Valparaiso and Delphi. They spent the night at Delphi
before continuing on to Indianapolis today.
</TEXT>
