<FIRST>r a PM-ArenaShooting     07-10 0308</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Arena Shooting,0317</SECOND>
<HEAD>Feud Between Band Crews Leaves One Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Feuding between roadcrews of two pop bands
erupted into a brawl that left one man dead and another in serious
condition today.
   The fighting culminated before a concert could begin here Sunday
when roadcrew members for New Edition and Guy battled with baseball
bats, microphones and other weapons, authorities said.
   The stagehands were setting up for the Budweiser Superfest
concert at the Civic Arena, police said. Five men ended up in jail,
one in the hospital and one dead. The concert was canceled.
   Crewmembers for the same groups got into a fistfight on stage
during a performance Saturday night in Greensboro, N.C.,
interrupting the concert for nearly an hour while a near sellout
crowd looked on and jeered.
   Commander Ronald Freeman of the Pittsburg police said the feud
started when Guy played beyond its time limit. When members of New
Edition came on stage, one of the members of Guy kicked or pushed
some of equipment belonging to New Edition.
   Anthony Bee, 32, of New York City, road security manager for Guy,
died Sunday of gunshot wounds to the chest and shoulders, according
to Mercy Hospital spokesman Eric Hofmann.
   New Edition's production manager, Ronald Byrd, 30, of Buffalo,
N.Y., was jailed on a criminal homicide charge and a firearms
violation in connection with Bee's death.
   Police also arrested Michael Floyd, Jean Griffith, Ronald Thomas
and Vincent Rosario, all of New York City. They were charged with
aggravated assault and criminal conspiracy in the beating of Michael
Clark, also of New York.
   Clark, a crew worker for New Edition, was listed in serious
condition this morning in Allegheny General Hospital.
   Police said Bee was shot in the back by a man who chased him out
of the arena and across the street into a hotel.
</TEXT>
