<HEAD>West German Astronauts to be on Shuttle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NASA and West Germany signed an agreement
Monday paving the way for two German astronauts and scientific
payloads to be included on the space shuttle in 1992.
   The agreement sets terms for reimbursement when NASA flies the
D-2 Spacelab mission with German materials processing and life
sciences experiments. West Germnay also has paid earnest money for a
mission scheduled for November 1993.
