cargo bay, was made in November 1985. The crew included one Dutch
and two German payload spcialists.
   Monday's agreement was signed by NASA Administrator Richard H.
Truly and Heinz Riesenhuber, federal minister for research and
technology of the Federal Republic of Germany.
