years, Margaret, became final three days before the June 18
elections. His open affair and a series of banking and financial
scandals contributed to the Socialist leader's failure to win a
third term in office.
   He and Ms. Liana were expected to marry soon after the elections,
but the wedding apparently was delayed by Papandreou's
hospitalization last month with pneumonia and kidney failure. He has
since recovered.
   Ms. Liani has been accused in the press of exerting pressure on
government ministers and creating a ``court'' around Papandreou that
isolated him from his friends and four children.
