<HEAD>$Adv12</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Wed AMs, July 12 and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-AP Arts: Bond Films</HEAD>
<HEAD>Bonded Beauties</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ever since a leggy and wet Ursula Andress
emerged from the Caribbean with snorkel and knife as the sultry
Honey Ryder in 1962's ``Dr. No,'' beautiful women have been a key
element in the successful James Bond cinematic formula. Here is a
list of all 16 authorized ``Bond girls,'' given in order of actress,
character, film and year of release:
   Ursula Andress, Honey Ryder. ``Dr. No'' (1962).
   Daniela Bianchi, Tatiana Romanova. ``From Russia With Love''
(1963).
   Honor Blackman, Pussy Galore. ``Goldfinger'' (1964).
   Claudine Auger, Domino. ``Thunderball'' (1965).
   Mie Hama, Kiss Suzuki. ``You Only Live Twice'' (1967).
   Diana Rigg, Tracy Vicenzo. ``On Her Majesty's Secret Service''
(1969).
   Jill St. John, Tiffany Case. ``Diamonds Are Forever'' (1971).
   Jane Seymour, Solitaire. ``Live and Let Die'' (1973).
   Britt Ekland, Mary Goodnight. ``The Man With the Golden Gun''
(1975).
   Barbara Bach, Maj. Anya Amasova. ``The Spy Who Loved Me'' (1977).
   Lois Chiles, Holly Goodhead. ``Moonraker'' (1979).
   Carole Bouquet, Melina Havelock. ``For Your Eyes Only'' (1981).
   Maud Adams, Octopussy. ``Octopussy'' (1983).
   Tanya Roberts, Stacey Sutton. ``A View to a Kill'' (1985).
   Maryam d'Abo, Kara Milovy. ``The Living Daylights'' (1987).
   Carey Lowell, Pam Bouvier. ``Licence to Kill'' (1989).
</TEXT>
