<FIRST>a a BC-SPE--Fashion:Hairstyle     07-10 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-SPE--Fashion: Hairstyle,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fashion: Hairstyle</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Hairstyles this fall will be softer and more natural looking,
says the man who calls himself Xenon, the international creative
director for the Helene Curtis Professional Division.
   ``Women are realizing that subtlety can be sexy,'' he says, and
are returning to the ``simple, elegant styling of the '30s and '40s.
This season's `hottest' looks will definitely be more `styled' than
before.''
   Hair will be worn shoulder length or longer _ or quite short _
with few variations in between, he says.
   He envisions longer hairstyles worn gently waved and full on the
sides by day, pulled back into sleek french twists for evening;
shorter hair will be smaller and less ``spiky'' than before,
following the shape of the head in a cap-like fashion.
   Bangs will remain an element for styles of all lengths, he says,
worn fuller, longer and brushed down instead of up.
</TEXT>
